68b33542-affb-490d-90ae-364e356db324	2024-08-06 20:07:17.551628+00	2024-12-23 00:46:10.309388+00	post/20c1770be9914d518c562b1f73f81e36.jpg	Black Business Growth Initiative Calls for Unity, Heritage	<h3><em><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Themed: &ldquo;Black Business Growth Initiative Celeb	black-business-growth-initiative-calls-for-unity-heritage	<h3><em><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Themed: &ldquo;Black Business Growth Initiative Celebrating our Heritage, Carrying it into the Future, Building Legacies</span></strong></em></h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #7e8c8d;">The event takes place next Wednesday, (20 September 2023), at the Personal Trust House in Rondebosch, Cape Town. The BBGI reflects itself as a community of like-minded people united for the growth of Black African businesses and careers. The BBGI is going to discuss the importance of the female voice in black matters; the truths and myths around Women&rsquo;s Day celebrations in South Africa; celebrating Black women with the support and buy-in of Black men.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #7e8c8d;">Black Business Growth Initiative celebrates our beautiful and diverse heritage. We carry our heritage into our very bright future.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #7e8c8d;">&ldquo;Through our individual heritage, we shall collectively build legacies for our nation.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #7e8c8d;">The BBGI asks several questions:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n<li><span style="color: #7e8c8d;">What aspects of your heritage do you want to take into the future to change the lives of your family and community?</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="color: #7e8c8d;">What baton was handed over to you, that you want to pass on to the next generation?</span></li>\r\n<li><span style="color: #7e8c8d;">Is your vision crystal clear and what tools do you have to chisel at this legacy every day?</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #7e8c8d;">Organisers are reaching out to the Black business community saying: &ldquo;Come join Black Business Growth Initiative, as we sit around the proverbial fire and discuss our heritage with an esteemed panel of experts.&rdquo;</span></p>	1	a05af2ea-1fcd-43be-bd35-3f996f75b6df
5ad109aa-054a-42bc-a1a7-90e1c3b80559	2024-08-06 20:10:14.530108+00	2024-12-23 00:47:09.295595+00	post/c4c0719a74624ee2ab0a971a4537ce7d.png	One hand can feed another”…a look at the phenomenon	<p><iframe style="width: 876px; height: 491px;" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/GoMqGk2hIV4?featu	one-hand-can-feed-anothera-look-at-the-phenomenon	<p><iframe style="width: 876px; height: 491px;" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/GoMqGk2hIV4?feature=youtu" width="876" height="491" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>	1	a05af2ea-1fcd-43be-bd35-3f996f75b6df
20930ddb-6b40-4c6c-91ee-24df037c912c	2024-10-19 10:51:31.414227+00	2024-12-23 00:48:04.143825+00	post/5d29649c267b42fd9b7ef8fb67d6b3d3.png	Entrepreneur Lessons: When marketing outruns service delivery readiness	On our website we encourage our community members to give ratings after receiving products or services for the businesses on our platform.	entrepreneur-lessons-when-marketing-outruns-service-delivery-readiness	<ul>\r\n<li>On our website we encourage our community members to give ratings after receiving products or services for the businesses on our platform.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It is encouraging to see that the reviews are largely positive.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We celebrate those.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We have found that for those few where the feedback is not good, the root cause is oftentimes that the business owners get more business than they are ready for.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is a critical matter for us to look into as business owners.</p>\r\n<p>The temptation is that we want as much business as possible. Sometimes, our marketing and sales are so good that we get more business than we can handle.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In these times, we need to be able to be honest with our clients and tell them what we can deliver realistically.</p>\r\n<p>We should avoid over-promising.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The positive experience of clients is a powerful marketing tool.</p>\r\n<p>The negative experience of clients is a dangerous thing that causes reputational damage and loses trust in your business brand and in you as a person.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The lesson, ask for help and be honest if you cannot deliver on expectations.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It means much more because - building trust is critical for sustainable business success.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sazi Ndwandwa CA (SA)</p>\r\n<p>MPhil (Leadership Coaching)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>About the Author</p>\r\n<p>Sazi Ndwandwa is a business and leadership coach.</p>\r\n<p>He is the CEO of GoldOurs (Pty) Ltd which helps companies and individuals to grow sustainably through three main service categories:</p>\r\n<p>- Direction and strategy</p>\r\n<p>- Talent management, leadership development, and training</p>\r\n<p>- Systems and processes including internal audit, accounting &amp; tax, and internal processes design &amp; reviews.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>	2	caee35c6-b0b9-4f1c-a4ed-d103955c72dc
18fa37ee-d640-4c68-9cab-327358fe433e	2025-12-03 21:00:36.512987+00	2025-12-03 21:03:19.115316+00	post/ff5e9beac4fb4ee9bf7eb85556ca3280.png	Alakhe Group Holdings: Building Sustainable Solutions for South Africa’s Future	In today’s rapidly changing economic landscape, South African businesses need more than just vision — they need partners who bring innovation, efficiency	alakhe-group-holdings-building-sustainable-solutions-for-south-africas-future-1	<p>In today&rsquo;s rapidly changing economic landscape, South African businesses need more than just vision &mdash; they need partners who bring innovation, efficiency, and long-term sustainability. <strong>Alakhe Group Holdings</strong> has emerged as one of the most searched and fast-growing Black-owned enterprises in South Africa, and for good reason. Their commitment to excellence, community upliftment, and innovative service delivery is positioning them as a leader in multiple sectors.</p>\r\n<p>As part of BBGI&rsquo;s mission to spotlight high-performing Black-owned businesses, we&rsquo;re proud to feature <strong>Alakhe Group Holdings</strong> as a business making a meaningful impact in the country.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Who Is Alakhe Group Holdings?</strong></h2>\r\n<p>Alakhe Group Holdings is a dynamic South African company offering a range of professional services designed to help businesses operate more efficiently and achieve sustainable growth. Backed by strong leadership and a passion for development, the company focuses on delivering real value to clients across both the public and private sectors.</p>\r\n<p>Their operations are rooted in:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Professional excellence</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Reliable service delivery</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Innovation-driven solutions</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Transformational economic participation</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>Key Services Offered by Alakhe Group Holdings</strong></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>1. Business Consulting &amp; Advisory</strong></h3>\r\n<p>The company provides strategic consulting services that help organisations improve performance, streamline operations, and unlock growth opportunities. Their advisory solutions are tailored to the unique needs of each business, ensuring measurable progress.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>2. Project &amp; Facilities Management</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Alakhe Group Holdings supports both small and large organisations with full project lifecycle management, from planning to execution. Their emphasis on efficiency and quality ensures that every project delivers long-lasting value.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>3. Construction &amp; Infrastructure Solutions</strong></h3>\r\n<p>From construction support to infrastructure-related services, the company is committed to building safe, modern, and reliable spaces that support economic development and community upliftment.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>4. Skills Development &amp; Training</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Understanding the importance of ongoing learning, the group offers skills programmes aimed at empowering individuals and improving workplace productivity. These programmes align with South Africa&rsquo;s long-term goals for inclusive growth.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>What Sets Alakhe Group Holdings Apart?</strong></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>⭐ <strong>A Commitment to Empowerment</strong></h3>\r\n<p>As a proudly Black-owned enterprise, Alakhe Group Holdings plays an important role in advancing economic inclusion. Their business model is rooted in creating opportunities and uplifting local communities.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>⭐ <strong>High Demand and Growing Visibility</strong></h3>\r\n<p>According to BBGI website analytics, <strong>&ldquo;Alakhe Group Holdings&rdquo; is currently among the most searched business names</strong>, showing strong public interest and trust in the brand. Their rapid rise in visibility demonstrates their growing reputation and influence in the market.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>⭐ <strong>Integrity and Professionalism</strong></h3>\r\n<p>The company operates with transparency and accountability &mdash; two qualities that consistently attract both new and returning clients.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Why BBGI Is Featuring Alakhe Group Holdings?</strong></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>At BBGI, we celebrate Black-owned businesses that are paving the way for excellence, empowerment, and economic transformation. Alakhe Group Holdings embodies these values through their service quality, leadership, and community-focused approach.</p>\r\n<p>This feature serves as both recognition of their growing impact and an invitation for South Africans to engage with and support their work.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong>How to Connect With Alakhe Group Holdings?</strong></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To learn more about their services, offerings, and latest projects, visit:</p>\r\n<p>👉 <strong><a href="http://www.alakhegroup.co.za/">www.alakhegroup.co.za</a></strong><br />👉 Connect through BBGI&rsquo;s business directory: <strong>bbgi.co.za</strong></p>\r\n<p>Supporting a Black-owned business today helps build the future we want to see tomorrow.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>	1	f4736bc4-bcb1-4576-9b6d-547e5e93a2c9
\.


