717eaa58-7419-4917-9484-b1a96225a062	2024-08-22 20:57:35.610186+00	2024-09-25 08:46:28.247329+00	event/e1f704898d8c4e2eb5ad9005161aa6fe.png	BBGI Family Market Day - October 2024	bbgi-business-market-heritage	<p>In celebration of family and creation of economic legacies, we invite business owners and buyers to come together to create positive memories for families, friends, and community.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There are 20 business stalls available for businesses in our community.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Sign your business up for our annual subscription at 50% off for R500. This also secures your stall to showcase your business and sell your products/services.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Bring your family and buy a R120 ticket. This will give you R100 spending coupons for the market day.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Join the BBGI community.</p>\r\n<p>Partner with us to transform Africa!</p>	Milnerton High School	Milnerton High School, 48 Pienaar Road, Milnerton, Cape Town, WC	\N	1	\N	2024-10-19 08:00:00+00	2024-10-19 14:00:00+00	Completed	84a0849e-c9da-40af-8098-df713cd527cc	2	Bringing Buyers and sellers together to build strong economic legacies.	0234567890	info@bbgi.co.za
81fbce18-bd33-4984-8dde-d0803b863af4	2024-09-04 03:56:10.657917+00	2024-12-23 00:23:28.294168+00	event/b3c5f494b1da46daae00b30ed843647b.png	Celebrating Black Excellence in our midst	celebrating-black-excellence-in-our-midst	<p>It is time to celebrate black excellence!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Join us as we celebrate the fruits of a transforming South Africa!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Help us celebrate those amongst us who are demonstrating excellence through the work they do... in the public sector, private sector, in academia, and in social impact non-profit spaces.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Join us as we share the good news, enjoy some entertainment, good food, positive vibes, and good company!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Get your ticket!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Now!</p>	Milneeton high School Conference Centre	Milnerton High School, 10 Pienaar Road, Milnerron, Cape Town	\N	0	\N	2024-10-30 17:00:00+00	2024-10-30 19:00:00+00	Completed	caee35c6-b0b9-4f1c-a4ed-d103955c72dc	2	Join us as we honour and celebrate our black professionals and business owners who are making impact! In private sector, academia, public sector, and social impact institutions! Join us as we demonstrate the positive, visible, and tangible fruits of a transforming South Africa!	info@bbgi.co.za	0234567890
1d2ee013-c950-418b-8203-372c0dc6d29e	2024-11-06 04:16:34.702818+00	2024-12-23 00:23:57.089812+00	event/6db9a687c87b41138551301db430235b.jpeg	Mental Health and Business	mental-health-and-business	<p>BBGIhosting our year-end- event focused on the vital role of mental health in professional success. Designed for Black entrepreneurs, business leaders, and professionals, this event will explore strategies for maintaining mental wellness while achieving business goals.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Date:</strong> Wednesday, 27 November 2024<br /><strong>Time:</strong> 6PM - 9PM<br /><strong>Location:</strong> Milnerton High School Conference Centre, Cape Town<br /><strong>Ticket:</strong> R210&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Gain valuable insights, connect with like-minded individuals, and build resilience for sustainable growth. Secure your seat today!</p>\r\n<p>For more information, contact us at <strong><a rel="noopener">info@bbgi.co.za</a></strong>.</p>	Milnerton High School Conference Centre,	Pienaar Road, Cape Town, WC, 7441, South Africa	-33.8729463,18.497128	32	\N	2024-11-27 16:00:42+00	2024-11-27 19:00:56+00	Completed	cbc243ff-6667-4a37-86ca-6ac0e06ee9e3	29	BBGI hosting our end-of-year event focused on the vital role of mental health in professional success. Designed for Black entrepreneurs, business leaders, and professionals, this event will explore strategies for maintaining mental wellness while achieving business goals.	info@bbgi.co.za	0658622202
37eb4c3f-58c3-4845-9d42-8ec91dc7452e	2025-02-05 14:46:45.437493+00	2025-02-13 05:37:51.906758+00	event/602c0ec988ea4bbda0aa403a8f12b800.jpg	BBGI The Pulse: Connecting Through Love, Business & African Legacy	black-business-growth-initthe-pulse-connecting-through-love-business-african-legacy	<p style="text-align: left;">We are hosting our first event of the year on Wednesday, 26th February 2025, our theme is The Pulse: Connecting Through Love, Business &amp; African Legacy. <br /><br />Love is an action that permeates every aspect of life, influencing not just you personally but also your professional journey and business endeavors. We are dedicating time to explore how love serves as a vital element for growth among Black individuals, their businesses, and their personal development, along with the legacy they create for their families and communities.</p>	Milnerton High School Conference Centre	Pienaar Road, Cape Town, WC, 7441, South Africa	-33.8729463,18.497128	15	\N	2025-02-26 16:30:22+00	2025-02-26 19:00:40+00	Completed	cbc243ff-6667-4a37-86ca-6ac0e06ee9e3	29	We are hosting our first event of the year on Wednesday, 26th February 2025, our theme is The Pulse: Connecting Through Love, Business & African Legacy.	info@bbgi.co.za	+27658622202
94595c09-fcef-49af-ae64-43d0cb29929f	2025-02-26 14:34:02.615986+00	2025-03-01 09:04:07.553448+00	event/ffd875b1353349bf9b9e31567007ddf9.jpg	BBGI March 2025, Our Human Rights Agenda: How to be an Active Agent for Transformation Where You Are	bbgi-march-2025-our-human-rights-agenda-how-to-be-an-active-agent-for-transformation-where-you-are	<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Human Rights Month is highlighted, in the South African calendar, by Human Rights Day which takes place on 21 March each year. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The history of South Africa was reshaped by ordinary people who decided to forego convenience, belonging, love, and even their lives so that black people could get the right to live freely in their home.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">We will come together as this community to remind ourselves of the importance of this memorial and to tighten our grip on the baton that has been handed over to us.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">We have an agenda to continue reshaping (South) Africa so that this freedom may be felt and enjoyed by more and more black people.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Get involved. </span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Join us.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>	22 on Sloane, Cape Town	39 Somerset Rd, Green Point, Cape Town, 8005	\N	5	\N	2025-03-27 16:30:48+00	2025-03-27 19:00:57+00	Completed	cbc243ff-6667-4a37-86ca-6ac0e06ee9e3	29	Black Business Growth Initiative 2025\r\n\r\nOur Human Rights Agenda: How to be an Active Agent for Transformation Where You Are	info@bbgi.co.za	+27658622202
daf86b68-62c5-429e-9161-d393a668e917	2025-05-13 13:01:54.074059+00	2025-06-02 14:25:50.385138+00	event/e68cfb50934b4da6be625366ec934257.jpg	Working & Thriving in Africa – Exploring Practical Financial Solutions	working-thriving-in-africa-exploring-practical-financial-solutions	<p class="" data-start="112" data-end="279"><strong data-start="115" data-end="158">BBGI 2025: Working &amp; Thriving in Africa- Exploring Practical Solutions&nbsp;</strong><br data-start="158" data-end="161" />Join us for a powerful evening focused on <strong data-start="203" data-end="236">practical financial solutions</strong> for business success across the continent.</p>\r\n<p class="" data-start="281" data-end="363"><strong data-start="285" data-end="300">26June 2025</strong></p>\r\n<p class="" data-start="281" data-end="363">&nbsp;<strong data-start="305" data-end="321">6:30PM &ndash; 9PM</strong><br data-start="321" data-end="324" /><strong data-start="327" data-end="363">Milnerton High School, Cape Town</strong></p>\r\n<p class="" data-start="365" data-end="456">Connect with industry leaders, finance experts, and entrepreneurs driving growth in Africa.</p>\r\n<p class="" data-start="458" data-end="512">📧 <a class="cursor-pointer" rel="noopener" data-start="461" data-end="476">info@bbgi.co.za</a><br data-start="476" data-end="479" />@blackbusinessgrowthinitiative</p>\r\n<p class="" data-start="514" data-end="614">&nbsp;</p>	Milnerton High School Conference Centre,	48 Pienaar Road, Cape Town, WC, 7441, South Africa	-33.8729434,18.4971753	0	\N	2025-06-26 16:30:07+00	2025-06-26 19:00:07+00	Completed	cbc243ff-6667-4a37-86ca-6ac0e06ee9e3	29	BBGI 2025: Working & Thriving in Africa\r\nJoin us for a powerful evening focused on practical financial solutions for business success across the continent.	info@bbgi.co.za	0658622202
880d02d2-b27e-4471-be06-1d0e65c1e6b6	2025-09-16 16:22:24.788593+00	2025-09-16 16:23:19.855343+00	event/13c6f41e8b704c6fa23b9484b0b385ac.png	Alakhe BuildHers - She Builds, She Leads, She Rises.	alakhe-buildhers-she-builds-she-leads-she-rises	<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Date: Saturday, 4 October 2025<br data-start="317" data-end="320" />Time: 10:00am &ndash; 13:00pm<br data-start="346" data-end="349" />Venue: Societi Sandton, Paradise City, 38 Wessel Road, Sandown, Sandton, Gauteng, South Africa</p>\r\n<p data-start="280" data-end="523">Tickets: R250 per person</p>\r\n<p data-start="280" data-end="523">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start="525" data-end="546"><strong data-start="528" data-end="544">How to Book:</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start="525" data-end="546">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul data-start="547" data-end="904">\r\n<li data-start="547" data-end="599">\r\n<p data-start="549" data-end="599">Purchase via<strong> </strong>Quicket &rarr; <a href="https://www.quicket.co.za/events/322093-alakhe-buildhers/#/">https://www.quicket.co.za/events/322093-alakhe-buildhers/#/</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="547" data-end="599">&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li data-start="600" data-end="904">\r\n<p data-start="602" data-end="623">Payment by EFT:</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="600" data-end="904">&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li data-start="626" data-end="679">\r\n<p data-start="628" data-end="679">Account Name: Alakhe Group Holdings (Pty) Ltd</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="682" data-end="703">\r\n<p data-start="684" data-end="703">Bank: Nedbank</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="706" data-end="740">\r\n<p data-start="708" data-end="740">Account Number: 1284724689</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="743" data-end="770">\r\n<p data-start="745" data-end="770">Branch Code: 198765</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="773" data-end="810">\r\n<p data-start="775" data-end="810">Account Type: Current Account</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="813" data-end="846">\r\n<p data-start="815" data-end="846">Reference: Your Full Name</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="849" data-end="904">\r\n<p data-start="851" data-end="904">Email Proof of Payment to: <a href="mailto:info@alakhegroup.co.za">info@alakhegroup.co.za</a></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="849" data-end="904">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p data-start="906" data-end="931"><strong data-start="909" data-end="929">What&rsquo;s Included:</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start="906" data-end="931">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul data-start="932" data-end="1067">\r\n<li data-start="932" data-end="969">\r\n<p data-start="934" data-end="969">Access to all sessions &amp; speakers</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="970" data-end="1021">\r\n<p data-start="972" data-end="1021">Networking opportunities with like-minded women</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="1022" data-end="1036">\r\n<p data-start="1024" data-end="1036">Goodie bag</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="1037" data-end="1067">\r\n<p data-start="1039" data-end="1067">Light lunch &amp; refreshments</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li data-start="1037" data-end="1067">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p data-start="1069" data-end="1169">Don&rsquo;t miss this chance to learn, grow and connect with other women shaping the business world.</p>\r\n<p data-start="1171" data-end="1224">Secure your seat today &ndash; limited spaces available!</p>\r\n<ul data-start="547" data-end="904">\r\n<li data-start="600" data-end="904">&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>	Societi	Wessel Road, Sandton, GP, 2128, South Africa	-26.0500935,28.0619208	0	\N	2025-10-04 08:00:54+00	2025-10-04 11:00:12+00	Completed	cbc243ff-6667-4a37-86ca-6ac0e06ee9e3	116	Alakhe BuildHers is a platform dedicated to empowering women entrepreneurs and women in corporate  through workshops, mentorship and peer support.	Info@alakhegroup.co.za	0634076116
ee429c8e-3824-4785-a891-20b322ee4e96	2026-02-05 06:24:55.786421+00	2026-02-13 10:53:25.64542+00	event/a754e42fd96840289345111bf98c5a63.jpg	Keys for Sustainable Growth & Success: Network and Business Relationships:	network-and-business-relationships-sustainable-success-growth	<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start="153" data-end="257"><strong data-start="153" data-end="178">BBGI Connect</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start="153" data-end="257"><br data-start="178" data-end="181" /><strong data-start="181" data-end="257">Theme - Sustaining Growth and Success: Network &amp; Business Relationships.</strong></p>\r\n<p data-start="153" data-end="257">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start="259" data-end="641">Defining success is personal. Building a successful business, career, or family requires growth. BBGI will be hosting an evening of dialogue and practical stories to explore the importance of relationships for growth and sustainable success.</p>\r\n<p data-start="259" data-end="641">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start="259" data-end="641">BBGI is the place for Black entrepreneurs, professionals, and creatives to grow together, share knowledge, and build relationships that create long-term impact.</p>\r\n<p data-start="259" data-end="641">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start="643" data-end="781">Come connect with like-minded individuals, exchange ideas, and become part of a community committed to the collective success and growth of black people.</p>\r\n<p data-start="643" data-end="781">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start="783" data-end="929">🎟 <strong data-start="786" data-end="806">Tickets are R200</strong><br data-start="806" data-end="809" />Secure your seat and invest in your network.</p>\r\n<p data-start="783" data-end="929">We will also have:</p>\r\n<p data-start="783" data-end="929">- live performance</p>\r\n<p data-start="783" data-end="929">- finger foods</p>\r\n<p data-start="783" data-end="929">- welcome drinks (0% alcohol)</p>\r\n<p data-start="783" data-end="929">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p data-start="931" data-end="993"><strong data-start="931" data-end="993">Purchase your ticket now and be part of the BBGI movement.</strong></p>	Milnerton High School	Pienaar Road, Cape Town, WC, 7441, South Africa	-33.8729434,18.4971753	5	\N	2026-02-26 16:00:24+00	2026-02-26 19:00:54+00	Completed	cbc243ff-6667-4a37-86ca-6ac0e06ee9e3	29	This year's theme is 'Sustaining Growth and Success'. This will be the golden thread for ur events during the year 2026.\r\n\r\nJoin BBGI for an evening that connects and empowers entrepreneurs, professionals, creatives,  and business leaders on how strong relationships drive long-term succcess.	info@bbgi.co.za	0662412015
